<A NAME=129Salinas School Dist.>
<H3><IMG SRC=script.gif ALIGN=left HSPACE=5>Salinas School Dist.</H3><BR>
AFTER MONTHS OF NEGOTIATIONS, SICK-OUTS AND PROTESTS. THE SALINAS UNION HIGH SCHOOL DISTRICT HAS FINALLY REACHED A CONTRACT AGREEMENT WITH ITS TEACHERS.
<P>
THE DEAL WAS MADE PUBLIC AT A PRESS CONFERENCE AT DISTRICT HEADQUARTERS THIS AFTERNOON.
<P>
IT INCLUDES A SIX PERCENT PAY RAISE RETROACTIVE TO LAST JULY, AND IMPROVED HEALTH BENEFITS.
<P>
"IT CATCHES US UP. WE WERE 16-TH OUT OF 17 IN TERMS OF PAY IN STATE. WE'RE NOT THERE YET.BUT NOT NEAR THE BOTTOM ANY MORE."
<P>
I ANTICIPATE RATIFICATION. SETTLEMENT IS FAIR, KEEPS THE DISTRICT SOLVENT, NEED TO HEAL THE WOUND.
<P>
EGAN SAYS HE'S CONFIDENT TEACHERS WILL VOTE IN FAVOR OF THE NEW CONTRACT THIS FRIDAY.
<P>
THE PLAN HAS THE FULL BACKING OF THE NEGOTIATING TEAM. AND THE EXECUTIVE BOARD.
<P>

